title.narrative: 3.3 CHILDREN, FAMILIES AND COMMUNITIES HAVE INCREASED CAPACITIES

description.narrative: Children, families and communities have increased capacities to promote practices to protect themselves and reduce violence., which contributes to Learning, Skills, Participation And Engagement, Prevention Of Harmful Practice, Promotion Of Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being And Justice, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Innovation, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Improved and equitable prevention of and response to violence, abuse, exploitation and neglect of children.

title.narrative: Children, families and communities have increased capacities to promote practices to protect themselves and reduce violence.

description.narrative: In 2021, 24,338 parents and caregivers (21,725 women and 2,613 men) benefited from positive parenting and child-rearing interventions, with 95 per cent having improved knowledge and skills as a result. Two extracurricular programmes on VAC in schools were developed and endorsed and will be rolled out in 2022. Engagement with religious actors resulted in adoption of a manual on child protection from the Islamic perspective. Targeted interventions raising awareness to reduce child labour reached 2,673 children (600 girl and 2,073 boy) and 2,541 adults (1,357 women and 1,184 men), including community-based organisations (CBOs) and private sector. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:22/12/2021
